https://www.dhs.gov/cisa/news/2019/06/22/cisa-statement-iranian-cybersecurity-threats?utm_source=cisa_slideshow&utm_medium=web&utm_campaign=dhsgov

The Department of Homeland Security's Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) released a statement on Iranian Cybersecurity Threats. In recent months, there has been a noticeable rise in 
Iranian actors targeting U.S. industry and government agencies. These Iranian attacks have been using "wiper" techniques, deleting massive amounts of data critical for businesses. These attacks are getting 
through using the same common tactics used by most hostile actors, spear phishing and credential stuffing. Keep using best practices and remember to be vigilant when it comes to your security.
